  <main id="main" class="container">
    <section class="card">
      <h2>What is Digital Marketing?</h2>
      <p>
        Digital marketing is the promotion of products or services through online channels.
        It helps brands reach the right audience, at the right time, with measurable results.
      </p>
      <div>
        <span class="pill">Measurable</span>
        <span class="pill">Targeted</span>
        <span class="pill">Scalable</span>
        <span class="pill">Always-on</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="types" class="card">
      <h2>Main Types of Digital Marketing</h2>

      <div class="types">
        <article class="type">
          <h3>SEO <span class="badge">Search Engine Optimization</span></h3>
          <p>Improve your site to rank higher in search results (Google, Bing).</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>On-page: titles, headings, content quality</li>
            <li>Technical: speed, mobile, sitemaps</li>
            <li>Off-page: backlinks, mentions</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>SEM / PPC</h3>
          <p>Paid ads on search engines (e.g., Google Ads) for instant visibility.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Keyword targeting & ad copy</li>
            <li>Landing page relevance</li>
            <li>Budget & bid strategy</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Social Media Marketing</h3>
          <p>Build awareness and engagement on platforms like Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, TikTok.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Content calendar & community</li>
            <li>Reels/shorts for reach</li>
            <li>Paid social for scale</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Content Marketing</h3>
          <p>Create valuable content to attract and retain an audience.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Blogs, guides, case studies</li>
            <li>Infographics & videos</li>
            <li>Topic clusters & internal links</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Email Marketing</h3>
          <p>Own your audience with newsletters, nurturing, and promos.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Lead magnets & signup forms</li>
            <li>Segmentation & automation</li>
            <li>Deliverability & testing</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Affiliate Marketing</h3>
          <p>Partners promote your products for a commission on sales.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Clear commission structure</li>
            <li>Trackable links & policies</li>
            <li>Partner enablement</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Influencer Marketing</h3>
          <p>Collaborate with creators who have your target audience.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Fit > follower count</li>
            <li>Brief, hooks, and CTAs</li>
            <li>Usage rights & disclosures</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Mobile Marketing</h3>
          <p>Reach users via mobile apps, SMS, push, and mobile-first design.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Responsive UX</li>
            <li>App analytics</li>
            <li>Location-based offers</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="type">
          <h3>Analytics & CRO</h3>
          <p>Measure performance and optimize conversion rates.</p>
          <ul class="list">
            <li>Goals, events, funnels</li>
            <li>A/B testing & heatmaps</li>
            <li>ROI tracking</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="comparison" class="card">
      <h2>Quick Comparison</h2>
      <table class="table" aria-label="Comparison of digital marketing channels">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Channel</th>
            <th>Speed</th>
            <th>Cost</th>
            <th>Best For</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>SEO</td><td>Slow → Compounding</td><td>Low–Med</td><td>Long-term organic growth</td></tr>
          <tr><td>SEM / PPC</td><td>Immediate</td><td>Med–High</td><td>Fast, targeted traffic</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Social</td><td>Fast</td><td>Low–Med</td><td>Awareness & engagement</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Content</td><td>Medium</td><td>Low–Med</td><td>Trust & education</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Email</td><td>Immediate</td><td>Low</td><td>Retention & sales</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section id="faq" class="card span-8">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <h3>How do I get traffic quickly?</h3>
      <p>Combine PPC for instant traffic with content and SEO for compounding results.</p>
      <h3>What should I track?</h3>
      <p>Track conversions, CPA/ROAS, organic rankings, CTR, and email engagement.</p>
    </section>

